# Copy to .env.local and fill in.

# --- LLM provider -----------------------------------------------------------
# `anthropic` (default) or `ollama` (local, free, no API key). If unset, the app
# uses Ollama automatically when OLLAMA_MODEL or OLLAMA_URL is set.
# LLM_PROVIDER=ollama
# OLLAMA_URL=http://localhost:11434
# OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.1:8b
#
# With the Ollama provider the ANTHROPIC_* credentials below are NOT needed.

# --- Anthropic credentials (only for LLM_PROVIDER=anthropic) -----------------
# Provide ONE of the two credentials below (the app prefers ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN).

# Option A — use your Claude subscription's usage instead of buying API credits.
# Mint a token with `claude setup-token` (requires a Claude Max plan) and paste it here.
# Caveat: driving a third-party app off subscription OAuth is a gray area of Anthropic's
# usage policy and may change without notice. See the README "Auth" section.
# ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=sk-ant-oat01-...

# Option B — a standard Anthropic API key (uses prepaid API credits; the sanctioned path).
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# Optional: override the models used by the pipeline.
# Route is a cheap classification call; Operate does the doc editing.
ROUTE_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
OPERATE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-5

# Optional: routing confidence below this goes to the Inbox instead of auto-applying.
ROUTE_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD=0.6

# Optional: where the SQLite file lives (defaults to ./data/ledger.db).
DATABASE_PATH=./data/ledger.db
